searchParameters.q: how to identify vintage wicker furniture

answerBox.snippet: Examine the Quality of the Materials and Construction Vintage wicker furniture was typically made from high-quality materials, such as rattan, reed, or willow. These materials are denser and heavier than modern synthetic wicker. The construction of vintage furniture is also different from modern pieces.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do I know what kind of wicker I have?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Simply take a look at its appearance, cheaper wicker looks like shiny vinyl and often very thin, so you wont ever be fooled! Quality wicker on the other hand is made out of Polyethylene, a type of eco-friendly synthetic resin that is infused with UV inhibitors to prevent fading from sun exposure.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can you tell the difference between wicker and rattan?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Rattan specifically refers to the stems of rattan palms, it is an organic, natural material. Wicker is a broad term referring to a woven pattern and nowadays is usually made of synthetic materials.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can you tell if a wicker basket is vintage?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet:
IDENTIFYING MARKERS OF AGE
1
Does the basket have a solid or carved wood handle?
2
Does the basket have some weight to it? Older baskets tend to be a little heavier.
3
What materials used? Oak splint and ash splint tend to be older baskets.
4
Does the basket have any reinforced areas? ...
5
Does the basket have a patina?
